      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even if your blood sugar is currently normal, skipping your basal insulin carries a significant risk of dangerous nighttime hypoglycemia, especially because your body's response varies from person to person. Basing decisions solely on a single fasting reading can be misleading, as insulin levels remain constant overnight regardless of recent food intake. It is crucial to speak with a pharmacist or endocrinologist as soon as possible; many medication guides explicitly warn against automatically omitting basal doses on days with very little food without professional adjustment.",
      "source": "target",
