      "content": "Even if your blood sugar is currently stable, relying solely on that reading is risky because basal insulin is programmed to work 24 hours, and taking it would likely suppress your glucose too much during the low-carbohydrate window you described. The \"common sense\" instinct to decrease insulin when eating less is often overridden by the unpredictable variability of your metabolism and other factors like stress or illness. You should consider checking your blood sugar again at 2:00 AM using your CGM app, wears, or a cheat sheet, and if it remains above a safe level, that data can be immediately shared with your doctor to signal if a temporary reduction is truly necessary.",
